        <hl1>Nascar Is a Contrivance</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Nascar at Crossroads After Years of Growth,'' April 15: Perhaps Nascar's popularity is not growing so fast because people realize that it is a monopoly and that there are forces at work to manipulate the outcomes of races. What was once a sport has become the equivalent of professional wrestling.</p>
        <p>Ted Stryker  Charlotte, N.C.</p>
      </block>
